title: Google\Cloud\Datastore\V1\QueryResultBatch
name: QueryResultBatch
description:
A batch of results produced by a query.

Generated from protobuf message google.datastore.v1.QueryResultBatch

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.skipped_results
params.description: The number of results skipped, typically because of an offset.

params.name: data.skipped_cursor
params.description: A cursor that points to the position after the last skipped result. Will be set when skipped_results != 0.

params.name: data.entity_result_type
params.description: The result type for every entity in entity_results.

params.name: data.end_cursor
params.description: A cursor that points to the position after the last result in the batch.

params.name: data.more_results
params.description: The state of the query after the current batch.

params.name: data.snapshot_version
params.description: The version number of the snapshot this batch was returned from. This applies to the range of results from the query's start_cursor (or the beginning of the query if no cursor was given) to this batch's end_cursor (not the query's end_cursor). In a single transaction, subsequent query result batches for the same query can have a greater snapshot version number. Each batch's snapshot version is valid for all preceding batches. The value will be zero for eventually consistent queries.

params.name: data.read_time
params.description: Read timestamp this batch was returned from. This applies to the range of results from the query's start_cursor (or the beginning of the query if no cursor was given) to this batch's end_cursor (not the query's end_cursor). In a single transaction, subsequent query result batches for the same query can have a greater timestamp. Each batch's read timestamp is valid for all preceding batches. This value will not be set for eventually consistent queries in Cloud Datastore.
